org.mundo.util.plugins
Class VirtualDirectoryJarFile

java.lang.Object
  java.util.zip.ZipFile
      java.util.jar.JarFile
          org.mundo.util.plugins.VirtualDirectoryJarFile

public class VirtualDirectoryJarFile
extends java.util.jar.JarFile

A VirtualDirectoryJarFile points to a directory (and not a JAR), but otherwise behaves exactly like a JarFile. i.e. Entries that are read from this particular JarFile instance are translated into file system calls.

Author:
AHa

Constructor Detail

VirtualDirectoryJarFile

public VirtualDirectoryJarFile(java.io.File dir)
                        throws java.io.IOException
Creates a new VirtualDirectoryJarFile for a given directory. The directory does not have to be present at the moment of creating the object, all methods that access entries of this JAR are looked up lazily when required.

Parameters:
dir - the directory to locate the element in
Throws:
java.io.IOException - never
